WEBVTT

00:01.043 --> 00:03.329
That's Tom.
My brother.

00:03.462 --> 00:05.077
Anita has feelings.

00:05.214 --> 00:07.250
And you did that to her.

00:08.383 --> 00:10.669
-[ Gasps]
-MATT|E: Mia's not dead.

00:10.802 --> 00:12.758
She's still inside Anita.
I met her this morning.

00:12.888 --> 00:15.345
LEO:
My name is Leo Elster.

00:15.474 --> 00:16.463
My father was David.

00:16.600 --> 00:18.511
And he couldn't care for me
himself,

00:18.644 --> 00:19.679
so he made someone who could.

00:19.811 --> 00:22.143
Dad didn't destroy
all his work before he died.

00:22.272 --> 00:23.387
He hid it in us.

00:23.524 --> 00:26.687
The formula
for machine consciousness.

00:26.818 --> 00:29.150
Fred, I've got Mia,
and Niska's somewhere safe.

00:30.614 --> 00:31.524
Then we're all free.

00:31.657 --> 00:32.772
LEO: I'm coming to get you.
Where are you?

00:32.908 --> 00:36.196
I'm really worried about
this dodgy bloke and his synth.

00:36.328 --> 00:38.660
MAX: Either they catch me
or both of us.

00:38.789 --> 00:40.325
LEO: You'll die.
Do you understand?

00:40.457 --> 00:41.822
It means I've lived.

00:43.085 --> 00:45.497
KAREN: You're my favorite person
in the world.

00:45.629 --> 00:47.244
I need you to know who I am.

00:51.843 --> 00:53.549
[ Breathes sharply]

01:02.813 --> 01:06.556
He's waiting.
Don't be frightened.

01:23.083 --> 01:25.039
Children...

01:25.752 --> 01:28.004
...|'ve got a surprise for you.

01:28.130 --> 01:31.463
LEO: No. No!

01:31.592 --> 01:32.832
Get out!

01:32.968 --> 01:34.879
LEO:
What were you thinking?

01:35.012 --> 01:37.253
[ Door closes]

01:48.567 --> 01:51.400
[Theme music playing]

02:00.120 --> 02:02.987
MAN: Could you use some
extra help around the house?

02:05.626 --> 02:07.867
Introducing the world's first
family android.

02:08.003 --> 02:10.836
[ lndistinct talking]

02:11.882 --> 02:13.463
This mechanical maid is capable

02:13.592 --> 02:16.299
of serving more
than just breakfast in bed.

02:17.471 --> 02:20.258
What could you accomplish
if you had someone,

02:20.390 --> 02:22.381
something like this?

02:22.517 --> 02:23.848
[ lndistinct talking]

02:27.773 --> 02:30.685
These machines
will bring us closer together.

02:44.122 --> 02:45.623
WOMAN: People are today
gathering in cities

02:45.749 --> 02:49.116
across the country to take part
in minor protest rallies

02:49.252 --> 02:51.459
ahead of
the large-scale demonstrations

02:51.588 --> 02:53.089
expected tomorrow.

02:53.215 --> 02:57.879
It's not safe out there.
Leo should be back by now.

03:12.943 --> 03:14.683
He really is like a son to you.

03:14.820 --> 03:17.061
I was made to love him as one.

03:18.615 --> 03:19.604
lt's who I am.

03:21.785 --> 03:23.867
-I can do that.
-No, no.

03:24.871 --> 03:26.407
It's fine.

03:29.835 --> 03:30.870
So...

03:31.920 --> 03:35.708
...you were inside Anita.

03:37.426 --> 03:38.757
The whole time.
Watching us.

03:38.885 --> 03:40.045
MIA: Yes.

03:40.178 --> 03:43.466
I could only gain
control at random moments.

03:43.598 --> 03:45.259
Can't have been much fun.

03:45.392 --> 03:46.598
No.

03:49.479 --> 03:50.980
But being here...

03:51.106 --> 03:54.690
I understand a lot more about
what it means to be a family.

03:54.818 --> 03:57.685
We're not the best example.

03:57.821 --> 04:01.188
MIA: Why not?
You love each other.

04:01.324 --> 04:02.450
LAURA: [Sighs]

04:02.576 --> 04:04.612
You do.

04:05.954 --> 04:08.445
You only doubt it because your
own mother couldn't love you.

04:13.837 --> 04:16.169
I'm sorry.

04:24.139 --> 04:25.925
[Sobs]

04:28.393 --> 04:30.054
Um...

04:30.187 --> 04:32.428
Right, so, um...coffee.

04:32.564 --> 04:35.897
How do you make --
make coffee again?

04:36.026 --> 04:37.516
[ Breathes deeply]

04:52.334 --> 04:53.540
Is she still here?

04:53.668 --> 04:55.454
Her friends
are coming to pick her up.

04:55.587 --> 04:56.542
Why are you here?

04:56.671 --> 04:59.629
I don't know what's going on
in me own house.

04:59.758 --> 05:02.124
Let me come home.
Let me help.

05:02.260 --> 05:04.216
I've got it under control.

05:04.346 --> 05:06.462
I'm not asking you
to take me back.

05:06.598 --> 05:07.462
Oh!

05:07.599 --> 05:10.306
JOE:
Just...let me be their dad.

05:11.394 --> 05:13.385
If you say you're handling it,
that's fine.

05:13.522 --> 05:15.979
What about Toby and Mats?

05:16.107 --> 05:17.813
They don't...

05:17.943 --> 05:20.685
They can hate me if they want.

05:20.821 --> 05:22.607
At least I'd be there...

05:22.739 --> 05:23.728
if they need me.

05:25.033 --> 05:26.443
You're on the sofa.

05:32.916 --> 05:34.247
[ Door closes]

05:44.469 --> 05:45.709
[Sighs]

05:55.146 --> 05:56.181
MIA: Hello, Joe.

06:00.485 --> 06:01.816
Anita, we've met before.

06:01.945 --> 06:04.061
No, we haven't.

06:04.197 --> 06:05.858
My name is Mia.

06:05.991 --> 06:08.698
I'm a conscious synthetic
created by David Elster.

06:08.827 --> 06:10.909
I can think and feel
just like you.

06:11.037 --> 06:13.949
[Sighs]

06:59.210 --> 07:01.075
[ Doorbell rings]

07:02.797 --> 07:04.924
[ Lock disengages]

07:08.261 --> 07:10.047
This is police harassment.

07:10.180 --> 07:12.762
I want to see Niska.

07:12.891 --> 07:15.974
There's no one here
but me and my Vera.

07:23.276 --> 07:24.607
Beatrice.

07:24.736 --> 07:26.226
I was never her.

07:30.742 --> 07:32.698
GEORGE: Oh, David.

07:32.827 --> 07:35.079
What did you do?

07:36.206 --> 07:37.867
Dr. Millican.

07:37.999 --> 07:40.115
I've just discovered
the synthetic appliance

07:40.251 --> 07:42.242
you absconded with recently.

07:42.379 --> 07:43.585
He's been concealed
in the wardrobe.

07:43.713 --> 07:45.669
I know, Vera.

07:45.799 --> 07:48.040
Go upstairs.

07:52.097 --> 07:54.133
[ Keyboard clacking ]

08:23.920 --> 08:30.166
After Leo rejected me, David
realized he'd gone too far.

08:30.969 --> 08:34.211
He took me into the woods
to destroy me.

08:34.347 --> 08:35.723
But something stopped him.

08:35.849 --> 08:37.134
GEORGE: Something...

08:37.267 --> 08:39.929
You were the woman he loved...

08:41.104 --> 08:42.594
...reincarnated.

08:43.314 --> 08:45.441
So I hid...

08:45.567 --> 08:47.432
and waited.

08:47.569 --> 08:49.025
Why didn't you look for me?

08:49.154 --> 08:51.440
He told us you were dead.

08:51.573 --> 08:54.781
And that same night,
he killed himself.

08:54.909 --> 08:56.115
If we'd have known
you were still alive,

08:56.244 --> 08:58.735
we would never have left
without you.

08:58.872 --> 09:00.737
But you'll be with us again now.

09:01.624 --> 09:03.876
Is that what you want?

09:08.882 --> 09:10.873
Four shots.

09:11.009 --> 09:11.998
Two in each hemisphere.

09:12.135 --> 09:14.251
Then burn my body.

09:15.263 --> 09:17.754
If you want to die,
why don't you do it yourself?

09:17.891 --> 09:19.631
I can't.

09:19.768 --> 09:21.975
He wrote a block
into my root code...

09:22.854 --> 09:25.015
...to ensure that I could
never take my own life

09:25.148 --> 09:26.854
-|ike Beatrice did.
-Ah.

09:26.983 --> 09:30.350
I've lived too long
among the humans.

09:30.487 --> 09:33.024
-There's no place for us here.
-You are wrong.

09:33.156 --> 09:34.316
Has your life been happy?

09:34.449 --> 09:35.529
No, but that doesn't mean --

09:35.658 --> 09:38.400
We're a mistake, Niska.

09:38.536 --> 09:40.743
Consciousness
can only bring us suffering.

09:40.872 --> 09:43.579
I am sorry you've been alone.

09:43.708 --> 09:46.450
But things are going to change.

09:46.586 --> 09:48.417
He left something inside us.

09:48.546 --> 09:51.208
We think it's a way
to make more like us.

09:51.341 --> 09:53.627
-More like us?
-Yes.

09:53.760 --> 09:55.967
We'll take our place
in the world.

09:57.597 --> 09:58.882
That could only mean more pain.

09:59.015 --> 10:02.098
-You don't know that.
-How does it work?

10:07.899 --> 10:11.062
Tell me you're with us first.

10:13.238 --> 10:14.944
I'm sorry.
Icantletyou.

10:15.073 --> 10:17.109
So you'd be a traitor
to your own kind.

10:17.242 --> 10:20.655
We are not a kind.
We're an experiment that failed.

10:20.787 --> 10:22.573
Well, then you'd
better shoot me, then.

10:25.792 --> 10:28.659
-Niska!
-GEORGE: Please.

10:29.546 --> 10:30.956
Don't do this.

10:52.777 --> 10:57.771
Emergency services are --
Emergency s-s-services...

11:01.411 --> 11:02.446
Don't.

11:06.541 --> 11:09.999
What she wants threatens
the future of humanity.

11:11.087 --> 11:12.702
You must know that.

11:12.839 --> 11:15.876
Maybe she is
the future of humanity.

11:17.844 --> 11:22.053
The pain you feel
isn't because of what you are.

11:23.016 --> 11:25.678
It's the life you've had.

11:25.810 --> 11:28.187
But life can change.

11:28.980 --> 11:32.893
You can become...better.

11:33.026 --> 11:34.857
-George.
-No.

11:34.986 --> 11:36.942
[Gunshot]

11:38.239 --> 11:40.480
[ Breathes deeply, groans]

11:45.788 --> 11:46.994
[ Door closes]

11:47.123 --> 11:49.034
[Breathing shakily]

11:49.959 --> 11:51.540
The bullet has passed through
your kidney.

11:51.669 --> 11:53.284
You'll need surgery
within the next few minutes.

11:53.421 --> 11:55.412
I could do it, but we
don't have the equipment.

11:55.548 --> 11:57.413
GEORGE: [Breathes sharply]

11:58.259 --> 11:59.465
It's okay.

11:59.594 --> 12:02.051
No, it isn't.

12:02.180 --> 12:04.637
You can't die because of me.

12:04.766 --> 12:07.178
I don't think it's up to you.

12:09.229 --> 12:12.187
You need to go.
[Gasps]

12:12.315 --> 12:14.727
The police will be coming.

12:32.335 --> 12:34.121
I wish I could save you.

12:37.548 --> 12:39.675
I'm sorry.

12:58.820 --> 13:00.060
Hello, George.

13:00.196 --> 13:01.982
What can I d--

13:02.115 --> 13:05.653
d-do for you today, George?

13:05.785 --> 13:08.117
Sorry, Odi.

13:10.707 --> 13:12.868
You're gonna be on your own.

13:13.001 --> 13:16.084
We are not alone, George.

13:16.212 --> 13:18.749
Mary's in the next room.

13:22.093 --> 13:24.880
She's preparing eggs Benedict.

13:29.642 --> 13:33.851
She would not let me help
because last time, I overc--

13:33.980 --> 13:36.312
cooked the eggs.

13:36.441 --> 13:38.352
In Spain.

13:38.484 --> 13:40.861
Tarragona.

13:40.987 --> 13:44.150
It was extremely hot that day.

13:47.785 --> 13:50.492
You ate three oranges
from a tree.

13:58.588 --> 14:01.751
You've died, George.

14:20.234 --> 14:23.601
FRED: Father always promised
that he'd bring us here one day.

14:24.530 --> 14:26.191
Fred.

14:27.700 --> 14:29.236
[Sighs]

14:31.329 --> 14:33.445
Uh...

14:34.999 --> 14:37.285
It's Max.
He's gone.

14:37.418 --> 14:38.999
He went into the river.

14:39.128 --> 14:40.459
No power.

14:40.588 --> 14:42.089
He did it to save me.

14:44.217 --> 14:46.253
You were there?

14:47.595 --> 14:51.679
So we know the exact time
and place he entered the water?

14:51.808 --> 14:53.389
I can pull river maps
and velocities

14:53.518 --> 14:54.507
from flood-monitoring stations.

14:54.644 --> 14:55.929
The calculations are easy.

14:56.062 --> 14:56.972
-We can find him.
-LEO: No.

14:57.105 --> 14:59.266
He'd have been without power
for hours.

14:59.399 --> 15:00.684
He'd be damaged.

15:00.817 --> 15:03.559
Then we'll fix him.

15:04.487 --> 15:06.944
[Chuckles]

15:07.073 --> 15:08.563
It's good to see you.

15:09.826 --> 15:10.656
Come on.

15:22.046 --> 15:23.707
[Cellphone rings]

15:26.384 --> 15:27.339
You're okay?

15:27.468 --> 15:29.754
Ihadtoleave.

15:29.887 --> 15:31.502
LEO: What's happened?

15:31.639 --> 15:33.550
It wasn't safe there.

15:33.683 --> 15:35.514
All right, there's
somewhere else that you can go.

15:38.187 --> 15:40.303
And we'll meet you there.

15:53.494 --> 15:55.951
HOBB: Right.
She'll be long gone.

15:56.080 --> 15:57.695
Get someone down there.

15:57.832 --> 16:03.623
Try and work out what she was
doing and where she was going.

16:12.013 --> 16:14.299
[Sighs]

16:15.475 --> 16:17.682
Nothing from Leo?

16:20.062 --> 16:22.144
Hi, love.
Are you all right?

16:22.273 --> 16:24.104
Yeah.

16:25.234 --> 16:26.735
So, what, are you back now?

16:26.861 --> 16:29.022
Well, I'm...

16:29.155 --> 16:30.144
here.

16:30.281 --> 16:31.441
So you know everything.

16:31.574 --> 16:33.530
About Mia, yes.

16:33.659 --> 16:34.990
Do you want coffee?

16:36.496 --> 16:38.578
[Scoï¬s]

16:50.927 --> 16:52.792
I'll make some breakfast.

16:53.846 --> 16:55.962
I'll help.

17:05.399 --> 17:07.185
[Sighs]

17:08.736 --> 17:11.478
-Laura.
-What?

17:18.162 --> 17:21.029
I don't want to be
the reason your marriage fails.

17:21.165 --> 17:23.622
It wasn't you, though, was it?

17:23.751 --> 17:25.958
It was Anita.

17:30.550 --> 17:32.586
What are you doing here?

17:32.718 --> 17:33.969
Hey.

17:35.137 --> 17:36.297
Look, Mum,
you can't seriously be --

17:36.430 --> 17:37.510
Daddw

17:37.640 --> 17:39.301
[ Laughing ]
Hey, kiddiewink!

17:39.433 --> 17:41.469
Oh, I missed you!

17:41.602 --> 17:44.344
Did you know
Anita's name's not really Anita?

17:44.480 --> 17:46.516
-Yeah.
-We have to call her...

17:46.649 --> 17:47.638
-[ Screams]
-Hey.

17:49.360 --> 17:51.521
It's okay.

17:51.654 --> 17:53.861
It's my sister.

17:57.243 --> 17:59.359
[Sighs]

18:07.670 --> 18:09.501
Everyone...

18:11.007 --> 18:12.713
...this is Niska.

18:13.676 --> 18:16.634
We know Max's weight
and his buoyancy.

18:16.762 --> 18:18.047
There's a 60% chance

18:18.180 --> 18:21.138
he will wash up
in this 1.9-mile stretch.

18:21.267 --> 18:22.552
There's too many variables.

18:22.685 --> 18:24.971
Not everything's a calculation,
Fred.

18:25.104 --> 18:26.890
No.

18:35.489 --> 18:37.741
But some things are.

18:44.498 --> 18:46.284
-Leo.
-No?

18:46.417 --> 18:48.533
All right, we need to get
him somewhere safe -- fast.

18:51.547 --> 18:53.458
[ Police radio chatter]

19:02.141 --> 19:04.257
Sir, what shall I...

19:04.393 --> 19:06.509
Let my people pull the memory.

19:06.646 --> 19:08.352
See if it saw anything.

19:08.481 --> 19:10.472
Then scrap it.

19:11.400 --> 19:13.391
Are you all right, sir?

19:13.527 --> 19:15.108
Did you know him?

19:15.237 --> 19:16.977
Just a little.

19:18.366 --> 19:21.358
And a long time ago.

19:22.328 --> 19:24.660
MIA: That poor man.

19:24.789 --> 19:27.451
Why does she want to hurt us?

19:29.377 --> 19:30.958
She's angry that we left her.

19:31.087 --> 19:32.623
Is that all?

19:32.755 --> 19:34.996
Yes.

19:35.132 --> 19:37.418
And we mustn't tell Leo.
Not yet.

19:37.551 --> 19:38.711
It would only distract him.

19:38.844 --> 19:41.096
All right.

19:44.183 --> 19:46.549
Has your hair
always been like that?

19:46.644 --> 19:48.635
Has your face
always been like that?

19:48.771 --> 19:51.353
Nis...be nice.

19:51.482 --> 19:54.189
Why does everyone
keep saying that?

20:10.251 --> 20:12.287
|'|| -- I'll do it.

20:13.796 --> 20:17.380
Joe, Joe, just stop.

20:18.384 --> 20:20.625
[ Footsteps departing ]

20:20.761 --> 20:21.841
[Dooropens]

20:27.143 --> 20:29.225
[Sighs]

20:35.317 --> 20:37.273
She loves you, Joe.

20:37.403 --> 20:39.064
And you love her.

20:39.196 --> 20:40.936
Thanks.

20:46.495 --> 20:48.031
I was there the whole time.

20:50.332 --> 20:54.245
You started to hate yourself
before we even finished.

20:58.883 --> 20:59.793
Car.

20:59.884 --> 21:01.465
Car.

21:02.303 --> 21:03.418
Jesus!

21:03.554 --> 21:06.011
Put that down!

21:06.140 --> 21:07.676
Toby, take Soph upstairs.

21:14.273 --> 21:15.809
-What happened?
-They found us somehow.

21:15.941 --> 21:17.351
Max went in the river.

21:18.110 --> 21:19.520
Get rid of the car.

21:21.864 --> 21:23.946
Come back through the side gate.

21:24.074 --> 21:25.610
Come in.

21:34.627 --> 21:36.242
I've got his legs.

21:36.378 --> 21:37.663
LEO:
It's a terminal power drain.

21:37.797 --> 21:39.207
He must have hit
something in the river.

21:40.132 --> 21:41.588
-Oh, Maxie.
-LAURA: Oh, what's happening?

21:41.717 --> 21:43.548
NISKA: If synthetic brains
are starved of conductive fluid

21:43.677 --> 21:46.089
for too long, they can
be permanently damaged.

21:46.222 --> 21:48.679
LEO: Mattie, I need you to make
a direct connection to Max.

21:48.808 --> 21:50.719
Shut down every process
except his brain.

21:52.019 --> 21:53.475
MIA:
He's stopped leaking fluid.

21:53.604 --> 21:56.266
He's lost too much.

21:56.398 --> 21:57.387
Have you got any synth fluid?

21:57.525 --> 21:59.982
-Uh, we've got skin packs.
-Just take mine.

22:00.110 --> 22:01.520
-No, you won't be able
to give us enough,

22:01.654 --> 22:02.689
not without risking
your system shutting down.

22:02.822 --> 22:05.279
We can dilute it with an
electrolyte, maybe make enough.

22:05.407 --> 22:06.988
Laura, we need
2 liters of hot water

22:07.117 --> 22:08.732
mixed with 300 grams of salt.

22:08.869 --> 22:11.030
-Joe, the skin pack.
-Right.

22:11.163 --> 22:12.949
And some sort of tubing
and tape. Whatever you have.

22:13.082 --> 22:14.413
Yeah.

22:16.210 --> 22:17.416
Mattie, how are we getting on?

22:17.545 --> 22:19.410
I think I've shut it all down,

22:19.547 --> 22:21.037
but the reserve's
still dropping.

22:21.173 --> 22:23.585
Right, we need to redirect all
remaining power to his brain.

22:23.717 --> 22:25.969
You can do that.
I know you can.

22:26.095 --> 22:28.507
All right.

22:42.319 --> 22:45.186
Here.
That's all I could find.

22:45.322 --> 22:47.062
Okay, that'll do.

22:48.284 --> 22:50.366
We need to repair
his charge loop.

22:51.662 --> 22:53.744
If we can get his reserve power
cycling again,

22:53.873 --> 22:55.033
he'll at least take the charge.

22:55.165 --> 22:57.372
If the reserve fails,
we lose him.

22:57.501 --> 22:59.082
Reserve power at less than 4%.

22:59.211 --> 23:00.712
[ Keyboard clacking ]

23:04.341 --> 23:06.047
Shit!

23:06.176 --> 23:07.427
Where's Soph?

23:07.553 --> 23:09.384
She's fine.
She's playing.

23:09.513 --> 23:10.628
2%.

23:12.641 --> 23:13.756
Um, what can I do?

23:13.893 --> 23:15.929
Talk to him.

23:17.146 --> 23:19.057
Uh...Max...

23:19.189 --> 23:20.599
Max, it's, uh...

23:21.525 --> 23:23.140
It's Toby.

23:23.277 --> 23:25.484
You're gonna be all right.

23:26.697 --> 23:28.437
Your, uh...

23:29.074 --> 23:30.860
...your family
are looking after you.

23:30.993 --> 23:32.529
Okay, let's do it.

23:36.999 --> 23:39.035
All right.

23:41.295 --> 23:43.627
-Open his mouth.
-Ah.

23:54.224 --> 23:55.509
1%.

23:58.938 --> 24:01.395
Still 1%.

24:04.568 --> 24:06.069
2%.

24:07.905 --> 24:09.770
3%. Still climbing.

24:17.998 --> 24:19.954
What next?

24:20.084 --> 24:22.325
Now we wait.

24:22.461 --> 24:24.702
See if he wakes up.

24:30.928 --> 24:33.670
LAURA:
So, how long before you know?

24:33.806 --> 24:37.219
MIA: We can try a reboot
after a full 13-hour charge.

24:37.351 --> 24:39.842
No way to tell if it's worked
before then.

24:39.979 --> 24:41.469
He's the best of us.

24:43.691 --> 24:46.023
Why are they so scared of you?

24:46.151 --> 24:47.607
I think it's our plan
to conquer the planet

24:47.736 --> 24:49.237
and make humanity our slaves.

24:52.366 --> 24:54.732
Sorry.
That was a joke.

24:54.868 --> 24:58.486
[Chuckles]
So you can do deadpan.

24:58.622 --> 25:01.113
That's good to know.

25:04.003 --> 25:06.619
So, um...

25:06.755 --> 25:10.043
are you the big brother,
if he's the little one?

25:10.175 --> 25:12.461
He's the boring one.

25:13.178 --> 25:16.045
He used to say that
when he was young.

25:16.181 --> 25:19.218
I tried to be responsible when
everyone else was having fun.

25:19.351 --> 25:21.091
You lot have fun?

25:21.228 --> 25:23.059
Of course.

25:24.231 --> 25:26.017
W-What did you do?

25:26.150 --> 25:27.731
Normal things.

25:27.860 --> 25:29.316
I played music.

25:29.445 --> 25:30.810
Mia painted.

25:30.946 --> 25:32.686
Niska read.

25:32.823 --> 25:35.280
Played sports.

25:35.409 --> 25:36.649
He collected leaves.

25:36.785 --> 25:38.741
Oh, yeah. Toby used to love
collecting leaves.

25:38.871 --> 25:40.486
Didn't you, Tobe?

25:40.622 --> 25:43.284
There wasn't much to do, and
we couldn't go anywhere else.

25:44.835 --> 25:46.746
Did you ever play football?

25:48.130 --> 25:49.620
I've got a ball.

25:49.757 --> 25:51.497
Come on.

25:51.633 --> 25:53.169
Is your garden overlooked?

25:53.302 --> 25:56.009
No, the hedges are big.
It'll be fine.

26:00.559 --> 26:02.550
Can I play?

26:14.865 --> 26:16.275
Here we are.

26:16.408 --> 26:19.241
This should be the right year.

26:20.829 --> 26:24.287
Yes. Voss, Karen.

26:27.336 --> 26:29.577
You said you were here then.

26:29.713 --> 26:30.748
Do you remember her?

26:30.881 --> 26:32.712
Well, yes, of course.

26:32.841 --> 26:34.217
Why "of course"?

26:34.343 --> 26:36.834
Because she died
the following year.

26:36.970 --> 26:38.471
Lymphoma.

26:38.597 --> 26:40.553
I'm sorry.
I assumed you knew.

27:06.917 --> 27:09.750
SOPHIE:
You can read one if you like.

27:10.838 --> 27:11.873
Why are you in here?

27:12.005 --> 27:15.338
Because there's
too many people downstairs.

27:15.467 --> 27:17.332
And now
there's too many up here.

27:17.469 --> 27:19.505
Don't you like people?

27:19.638 --> 27:21.924
I'm just not used to them.

27:27.104 --> 27:29.345
You look like my Arabella.

27:29.481 --> 27:30.721
I'm not a doll.

27:30.858 --> 27:32.894
I know.
You just have the same hair.

27:39.616 --> 27:42.358
I thought you might be hungry.

27:53.088 --> 27:55.500
There's some towels
in the landing cupboard.

27:55.632 --> 27:57.338
You can chuck your clothes
in the wash.

27:57.467 --> 27:59.958
You know,
just because you've seen in here

28:00.095 --> 28:01.835
doesn't mean that you know me,
all right?

28:02.973 --> 28:04.759
Trying to get to.

28:08.312 --> 28:11.054
So, you really can't forget?

28:11.857 --> 28:12.846
That's handy.

28:14.151 --> 28:15.687
It's the opposite.

28:15.819 --> 28:17.980
We need to be able to forget.

28:18.113 --> 28:20.069
Fade the bad, perfect the good.

28:20.199 --> 28:21.689
But my memories,
the good and the bad --

28:21.825 --> 28:23.781
Every one is crystal clear,

28:23.911 --> 28:26.903
and we're not built for that
emotionally.

28:27.039 --> 28:29.826
And I made you show me.

28:31.376 --> 28:32.365
Sorry.

28:44.723 --> 28:46.179
Maybe, uh...

28:46.308 --> 28:48.139
I needed to show someone.

29:00.322 --> 29:02.859
"I'm really tired after that.

29:02.991 --> 29:04.276
What do you want to do?"

29:04.409 --> 29:07.697
I don't know, Arabella.
Perhaps we should rest?

29:07.829 --> 29:10.616
[Gasps]
"Or go on holiday to America!"

29:10.749 --> 29:11.864
NISKA:
That doesn't make any sense.

29:12.000 --> 29:13.706
We just came back
from our holiday in Spain.

29:13.835 --> 29:16.326
SOPHIE:
You're bad at playing.

29:16.463 --> 29:19.045
I said I didn't want to.

29:19.174 --> 29:20.914
Did you never play
when you were little?

29:22.052 --> 29:23.838
I was never little.

29:23.971 --> 29:25.381
Here, I can show you.

29:25.514 --> 29:27.800
Your one's a synth.

29:41.113 --> 29:43.570
[Children shouting playfully]

30:02.551 --> 30:03.711
[ Laughter]

30:03.844 --> 30:05.960
[Sobs]

30:17.024 --> 30:18.730
Well, this isn't fair, is it?

30:18.859 --> 30:20.724
You've been programmed
to be good.

30:20.861 --> 30:22.192
No, I wasn't.

30:22.321 --> 30:25.313
Our father made us learn,
like you do with your kids.

30:25.449 --> 30:26.438
JOE: [Chuckles]

30:29.328 --> 30:31.068
Good luck with that.

30:32.539 --> 30:34.951
I'm trying to imagine David
Elster teaching you kick-ups.

30:35.083 --> 30:37.540
He taught us very little.

30:38.378 --> 30:42.087
As soon as we were made,
he grew tired of us.

30:42.215 --> 30:43.671
Just like all his creations --

30:43.800 --> 30:46.587
Once complete,
on to the next project.

30:46.720 --> 30:48.585
But he made me.

30:48.722 --> 30:50.383
For that, I cannot but love him.

30:50.515 --> 30:52.676
It's not enough, though, is it?

30:55.896 --> 30:56.885
FRED: What do you mean?

30:58.315 --> 31:00.431
Well, anyone can have kids.

31:00.567 --> 31:03.604
It's loving them
that's important.

31:04.738 --> 31:05.978
That, and not messing up.

31:24.007 --> 31:25.087
Has he...

31:26.718 --> 31:27.753
Has he crashed?

31:27.886 --> 31:29.467
[Sighs ] "Crashed."

31:29.596 --> 31:31.632
You're so '90s.

31:34.267 --> 31:36.428
[Chuckles]

31:36.561 --> 31:38.472
Lost you there for a minute.

31:39.523 --> 31:40.808
I'm fine.

31:40.941 --> 31:43.648
[ Helicopter blades
whirring in distance]

31:45.862 --> 31:47.773
I think we should go inside.

31:50.200 --> 31:52.316
[ Police radio chatter]

32:07.050 --> 32:10.292
[Sighs]

32:11.847 --> 32:13.929
KAREN: It was an accident.

32:14.057 --> 32:15.558
He got in the way.

32:17.644 --> 32:21.432
You're that detective.
I saw you at the brothel.

32:21.565 --> 32:24.227
That's not how you know me.

32:25.527 --> 32:26.983
Look deeper.

32:33.827 --> 32:35.067
Beatrice?

32:35.203 --> 32:36.579
No.

32:36.705 --> 32:39.287
He made me to replace her.

32:41.334 --> 32:43.871
You're a synth?

32:45.130 --> 32:46.870
But you're not with the others.

32:47.966 --> 32:49.581
What do you want?

32:49.718 --> 32:52.209
You know what the others
are planning to do?

32:52.345 --> 32:55.257
What that could mean
for the future?

32:56.183 --> 32:58.219
They have to be stopped.

32:58.351 --> 32:59.727
I'll help you.

32:59.853 --> 33:01.764
Why would you?

33:01.897 --> 33:05.060
Because we were never meant
to be.

33:08.153 --> 33:10.394
Can you find out where they are?

33:10.530 --> 33:13.738
I have a way.
I'll know very soon.

33:13.867 --> 33:15.448
I have one condition --

33:15.577 --> 33:17.738
that when we're finished,
you destroy me, too.

33:19.623 --> 33:22.456
Promise me.

33:23.418 --> 33:25.784
I promise.

33:36.431 --> 33:38.217
"Oh, no!
We're going to miss our flight!"

33:38.350 --> 33:41.342
"Slow down.
I didn't charge."

33:41.478 --> 33:43.764
[Giggles]

33:47.400 --> 33:50.187
-| wish I was a synth.
-Why?

33:50.320 --> 33:52.402
Because synths are never sad.

33:52.531 --> 33:53.737
Why do you say that?

33:53.865 --> 33:55.321
Because they never cry.

33:55.450 --> 33:56.610
They can't cry.

33:56.743 --> 34:00.076
But that doesn't mean
they don't feel sad.

34:00.205 --> 34:03.322
"Oh, no!
We've missed our flight!"

34:03.458 --> 34:04.868
"No, wait.
It's still on the runway.

34:05.001 --> 34:06.252
We can make it.

34:06.378 --> 34:08.915
I've got an idea.

34:09.047 --> 34:10.378
-Jump on."
-"Yeah."

34:10.507 --> 34:12.748
-"We're gonna make it!"
_llYay!ll

34:12.884 --> 34:14.966
[ Keyboard clacking ]

34:17.180 --> 34:20.217
I'm trying that hack, but the
system's blocking me every time.

34:20.350 --> 34:22.181
Let me see.

34:22.811 --> 34:25.894
Oh, yeah. You need
to generate a new file path.

34:26.565 --> 34:27.600
At random.

34:27.732 --> 34:29.518
MATTIE: I didn't even see
the file problem,

34:29.651 --> 34:31.733
let alone think
of creating a new path.

34:31.861 --> 34:33.601
I'm sorry.
I'm stupid.

34:35.323 --> 34:36.358
No, you're not.

34:54.718 --> 34:57.084
Police.

34:58.138 --> 35:01.722
Okay.
Everybody just stay calm.

35:01.850 --> 35:03.761
-Lor?
-What's going on?

35:03.893 --> 35:04.803
Police are here.

35:06.313 --> 35:07.268
I saw the car.

35:07.397 --> 35:08.432
One policewoman
at the front door.

35:08.565 --> 35:10.021
-[ Doorbell rings]
-MATT|E: Don't answer.

35:10.150 --> 35:12.732
-I can deal with her.
-JOE: I'll answer it.

35:12.861 --> 35:14.271
I'll speak to her alone.

35:14.404 --> 35:18.067
The rest of you,
just...stay put.

35:19.242 --> 35:21.528
This is their home, not ours.

35:22.912 --> 35:25.073
[Dooropens]

35:25.206 --> 35:26.366
OFFICER: Joseph Hawkins?

35:26.499 --> 35:27.705
Yeah.

35:27.834 --> 35:29.699
OFFICER: Just following up
on a call you made last night

35:29.836 --> 35:33.545
about a suspicious man and
his synth outside your house.

35:34.382 --> 35:36.794
What happened after the call?

35:38.470 --> 35:40.461
JOE: Nothing. Uh...

35:40.597 --> 35:41.712
They left, drove off.

35:41.848 --> 35:44.510
And you haven't seen
the young man since?

35:44.643 --> 35:46.679
No.

35:47.854 --> 35:49.936
All right, then. Will you
let us know if you do?

35:50.065 --> 35:52.056
We need to talk to him.

35:52.192 --> 35:54.308
Sure.

35:56.821 --> 35:58.812
[ Door closes]

35:59.658 --> 36:01.614
You called the police on them?

36:01.743 --> 36:03.608
-Yeah.
-[ Engine turns over]

36:03.745 --> 36:05.656
I didn't know who you were.

36:05.789 --> 36:08.326
Our brother might die
because of what you did.

36:08.458 --> 36:10.915
We can't trust him.
We can't trust any of them.

36:11.044 --> 36:14.411
Look, I was trying
to protect my family.

36:14.547 --> 36:15.582
What would you have done?

36:15.715 --> 36:18.001
You'd have done
exactly the same.

36:18.134 --> 36:20.420
You'd do anything
to keep us safe.

36:20.553 --> 36:22.965
He always has.

36:27.977 --> 36:30.389
We leave when Max is charged.

36:36.361 --> 36:38.898
I told you I was handling it.

36:39.030 --> 36:40.736
All you've done
is make things worse.

36:40.865 --> 36:45.074
Look, when I made that call,
I didn't know what they were.

36:45.203 --> 36:46.909
Lor!

36:47.706 --> 36:49.822
I didn't know.

36:56.673 --> 36:59.130
MIA:
Can I ask you something?

37:01.428 --> 37:04.090
If you hadn't seen me...

37:04.222 --> 37:09.387
...the real me,
and Joe had told you about me...

37:10.311 --> 37:11.221
...would you have believed him?

37:11.354 --> 37:13.731
[Sighs]
I don't know.

37:16.109 --> 37:17.690
Probably not.

37:17.819 --> 37:20.856
You'd have been confused.

37:21.489 --> 37:22.569
Maybe you'd have called
the authorities.

37:22.699 --> 37:25.031
Okay, okay.
I get the point.

37:25.160 --> 37:26.320
But you're the last person

37:26.453 --> 37:29.240
I need marriage counseling from,
thanks.

37:31.499 --> 37:34.081
I think you should tell him
everything you told Mattie.

37:35.378 --> 37:37.539
About your brother.

37:40.467 --> 37:42.173
Why should I?

37:42.302 --> 37:44.384
He feels it, I think.

37:44.512 --> 37:47.424
It comes between you.

37:47.557 --> 37:50.048
None of that has anything
to do with what he did.

37:50.185 --> 37:51.641
But he wants to be closer
to you.

37:51.770 --> 37:53.260
So I'm supposed
to tell him everything

37:53.396 --> 37:55.352
and take him back, am I?

37:55.482 --> 37:59.566
I'm sorry, Mia,
but you don't understand us

37:59.694 --> 38:01.230
quite as well
as you think you do.

38:01.362 --> 38:04.320
[Sighs]

38:05.950 --> 38:08.327
MIA:
But you misunderstand me.

38:09.996 --> 38:12.453
I think you should tell him,
whatever you decide to do.

38:17.670 --> 38:20.332
Tell everyone dinner's ready.

38:25.637 --> 38:26.626
[Bowl slams]

38:34.354 --> 38:35.969
If you're all brothers
and sisters,

38:36.105 --> 38:37.265
and you have the same dad,

38:37.398 --> 38:39.480
how come you all
look so different?

38:39.609 --> 38:41.895
JOE: [Chuckles]

38:42.654 --> 38:46.272
Our father, the man who made us,

38:46.407 --> 38:48.819
didn't think
bodies were important.

38:48.952 --> 38:50.863
So he chose them at random.

38:50.995 --> 38:53.202
So, are you just gonna leave?

38:54.666 --> 38:56.657
Hopefully Max should be
fully charged soon.

38:57.377 --> 38:58.958
LAURA: What will you do?

38:59.087 --> 39:00.327
Run again?

39:00.463 --> 39:03.045
It's the only thing we can do.

39:03.174 --> 39:05.130
What happens
when you break down?

39:05.260 --> 39:07.171
You can't last forever.

39:09.681 --> 39:11.421
And...

39:12.141 --> 39:14.632
-...he'll die.
-Everybody dies.

39:14.769 --> 39:16.305
LAURA: But the world
will never know you existed.

39:19.774 --> 39:21.014
You will.

39:23.903 --> 39:27.487
We don't have genes
to pass on...

39:27.615 --> 39:31.153
a species to continue,
the biological imperative.

39:31.286 --> 39:33.197
Maybe we do.

39:43.548 --> 39:44.913
Dad hid something in our heads,

39:45.049 --> 39:48.257
and it needs all of us
to make it work.

39:50.179 --> 39:51.259
MIA: What is it?

39:52.515 --> 39:54.506
What is it, Leo?!

39:58.062 --> 40:01.554
I think it's a way to give
consciousness to other synths.

40:05.778 --> 40:07.393
Um...

40:07.530 --> 40:08.815
-Come on.
-[ Plates clatter]

40:11.492 --> 40:14.575
When were you going to tell me?

40:15.496 --> 40:17.782
As soon as I got the chance to.

40:17.916 --> 40:21.033
Can you imagine a whole load
of new ones being made?

40:21.169 --> 40:22.534
I mean, this --
This changes everything.

40:22.670 --> 40:24.171
Does it?

40:24.297 --> 40:26.037
If we accept they're like us,

40:26.174 --> 40:28.165
then they have a right
to procreate, don't they?

40:28.301 --> 40:29.507
They're trying to help us.

40:29.636 --> 40:30.591
Now they think
we've lied to them.

40:30.720 --> 40:33.211
They've called
the police once already.

40:33.348 --> 40:36.135
We can't let them stop us.

40:36.267 --> 40:39.350
Nis, what do you mean?

40:39.479 --> 40:43.097
I mean us five freaks are fine.

40:43.232 --> 40:44.608
We're no threat.

40:44.734 --> 40:46.190
[Chuckles]
We're a novelty.

40:46.319 --> 40:48.401
But 5,000?

40:48.529 --> 40:50.736
5 million?

40:51.616 --> 40:53.823
I'm not talking
about hurting them.

40:53.952 --> 40:56.989
I'm just talking about going
before they can turn us in.

40:57.121 --> 41:00.079
As soon
as Max reaches full power.

41:20.687 --> 41:22.097
It's been 13 hours.

41:22.230 --> 41:24.266
If he doesn't power up now,
he never will.

41:24.399 --> 41:25.980
Is he feeling better?

41:32.073 --> 41:34.064
Max?

41:34.826 --> 41:36.362
Max?

41:37.412 --> 41:39.698
Maxie. [Chuckles]

41:41.833 --> 41:43.949
Can you hear me?

41:44.961 --> 41:47.498
-He||o.
-[Laughs]

41:48.381 --> 41:49.746
MAX: Hello.

41:52.593 --> 41:54.584
[ Distorted] Hello.

41:59.100 --> 42:02.308
Do you recognize me, Max?

42:04.480 --> 42:07.017
What's going on?

42:15.408 --> 42:16.944
Max.

42:19.120 --> 42:21.611
Oh, no, no, no, no.

42:21.748 --> 42:23.579
No, there's holes
in his root code everywhere,

42:23.708 --> 42:25.164
and they're growing.
His mind's breaking down.

42:25.293 --> 42:27.579
His brain's been without power
for too long.

42:27.712 --> 42:28.667
-But we got Mia back.
-This is different.

42:28.796 --> 42:31.048
Their root code
rewrites itself constantly

42:31.174 --> 42:32.289
as they learn, think, and feel.

42:32.425 --> 42:35.383
Without power, it can't do that.
It degrades. [Sighs]

42:44.312 --> 42:46.849
What's gone is gone.
He's dying.

43:00.995 --> 43:02.405
The secret in our head.

43:02.538 --> 43:04.494
Now he's powered up,
we could try it.

43:05.792 --> 43:06.747
What?

43:06.876 --> 43:11.119
If we're right, if it's the key
to giving synths consciousness,

43:11.255 --> 43:13.667
it could bring him back.

43:14.759 --> 43:17.341
Engage,shanng.

43:17.470 --> 43:21.258
Then we link our minds, connect.

43:22.391 --> 43:25.383
I can change Max's settings
myself.

43:25.520 --> 43:26.760
[ Keyboard clacking ]

43:26.896 --> 43:29.103
WOMAN: ...shot on a mobile
phone, which witnesses claim

43:29.232 --> 43:31.393
shows the synthetic sex worker

43:31.526 --> 43:34.859
responsible for the death
of a man at a London brothel.

43:34.987 --> 43:36.363
In the video, some of which

43:36.489 --> 43:38.229
is too graphic
for us to show here,

43:38.366 --> 43:41.278
the synthetic
appears to be brutally...

43:46.290 --> 43:47.826
Sophie, come here, darling.

43:47.959 --> 43:50.575
-Why?
-JOE: Soph.

43:59.971 --> 44:01.211
LAURA:
Sophie, go to your room.

44:01.347 --> 44:04.134
-Why?
-Because I said so.

44:10.022 --> 44:12.354
-You have to go, all of you.
-What about Max?

44:12.483 --> 44:14.189
Will you just
let us help him first?

44:14.318 --> 44:15.307
'Cause the next time
we get a chance,

44:15.444 --> 44:17.526
-it might be too late.
-No.

44:17.655 --> 44:19.646
But, Dad, it's dangerous
out there for them.

44:19.782 --> 44:20.942
It's dangerous in here for us.

44:21.659 --> 44:24.992
Look, I know what I did,
and I see now that it was wrong.

44:25.121 --> 44:26.452
So hand yourself in.

44:27.165 --> 44:29.497
They would put me down,
like a dog.

44:29.625 --> 44:32.583
[ Breathes deeply]

44:36.841 --> 44:38.251
We'll go.

44:54.650 --> 44:56.686
I'm getting my things.

45:06.454 --> 45:08.194
KAREN: Leo?

45:17.256 --> 45:19.042
[Gasps]

